title: High-school football | OCC roundup: Central Crossing comeback stuns Coffman
text:
Williamson completed 33 of 49 passes for 388 yards and five TDs. Gunner Hoak completed 19 of 30 passes for 302 yards and three TDs. 
Mount Vernon 46, Big Walnut 21 
Mason Williams completed 29 of 34 passes for 451 yards and seven TDs, and Mount Vernon (5-2, 2-2) defeated visiting Big Walnut (2-5, 1-3) in the OCC Capital. Nate Davis caught 11 passes for 145 yards and three TDs for the Yellow Jackets, who finished with 510 yards. Jacob Tiell caught seven passes for 101 yards and Owen Carpenter hauled in two TDs. 
Worthington Kilbourne 34, Franklin Heights 28 
Josh Stoner scored on a 20-yard run in overtime, and Worthington Kilbourne (7-0, 4-0) survived a scare from host Franklin Heights (0-7, 0-4) in the OCC Capital. Kilbourne led 27-13 in the fourth quarter behind two TDs each from Stoner and Isaiah Young, who finished with 184 yards rushing on 33 carries. Franklin Heights forced overtime when Seth Dawkins scored on a 3-yard pass and caught the conversion from Dylan Akers with 26 seconds left, capping an 80-yard drive. Franklin Heights turned the ball over on down on its overtime possession. Akers completed 21 of 36 passes for 302 yards. Dawkins had 229 all-purpose yards and scored three TDs. 
Hilliard Bradley 35, Canal Winchester 0 
Will Phillis completed 20 of 29 passes for 345 yards and four TDs, and Hilliard Bradley (4-3, 1-3) defeated visiting Canal Winchester (0-7, 0-4) in the OCC Cardinal. Kory Taylor caught all four of Phillis’ TD passes. He hauled in scores from 12, 31, 52 and 19 yards. He finished with nine catches for 244 yards. Bradley held Canal to 92 yards. 
Dublin Jerome 26, Dublin Scioto 0 
Zach Hazlett completed 17 of 29 passes for 253 yards and three TDs, all in the second quarter, and Dublin Jerome (3-4, 3-1) slowed host Dublin Scioto (2-5, 1-3) in the OCC Cardinal. Thomas Henderson caught TD passes of 5 and 26 yards, respectively, and Ty Henderson caught a 49-yard TD. Hazlett rounded out the scoring with a 6-yard run in the third quarter. 
Hilliard Darby 28, Westerville South 21 
Nick Powers had 187 yards rushing and scored a 1-yard touchdown run in overtime to help Hilliard Darby escape visiting Westerville South in an Ohio Capital Conference Cardinal Division game Friday night. Powers, who had 29 carries, gave the Panthers an early lead with a 49-yard TD run and Jake Snyder (95 yards rushing) scored twice in the second quarter for a Darby 21-7 lead. Westerville South’s Jaelen Gill scored a pair of second-half touchdowns - a 64 yard TD reception and a 1-yard run - to tie the game with 11:56 left in regulation, but Anthony Bonnell missed a 27-yard field goal with nine seconds remaining. 
Westerville Central 41, Westerville North 21 
Benny Snell rushed for 182 yards and scored four TDs, and Westerville Central (7-0, 4-0) handled visiting Westerville North (0-7, 0-4) in the OCC Cardinal. Snell scored on runs of 7, 11 and 25 yards. He also caught an 18-yard TD pass from Daniel Kreuzer, who had two TD passes. Shauon Rogers rushed for 83 yards and three TDs for Westerville North. 
Marysville 35, Thomas Worthington 7 
Thomas Rush had 136 yards rushing and two touchdowns, Nathan Snyder threw a pair of TD passes and Marysville (2-5, 1-3) rolled past Thomas Worthington (1-6,l 0-4) in the OCC Central. 
Olentangy Liberty 48, Westland 19 
Alex Lando had 212 total offensive yards with two touchdown runs and Olentangy Liberty (6-1, 3-1) defeated visiting Westland (4-3, 2-2) in the OCC Central. Lando, who had 150 yards passing and 62 rushing, helped give the Patriots a 28-7 lead in the second quarter on a 19-yard run. Brenden White added two touchdowns, a 68-yard punt return and a 98-yard kick return. 
Pickerington Central 46, Grove City 24 
Seth Currens accounted for three Pickerington Central touchdowns and the Tigers (5-2, 3-1) downed host Grove City (2-5, 1-3) in the OCC Ohio. Currens had 141 yards passing with a 37-yard TD pass to Trenton Gillison and added 48 yards on the ground with TD runs of 11 and 14 yards. Gillison finished with four receptions and 82 yards. Jeremy Ford had 150 yards passing and two TD passes for Grove City. 
Reynoldsburg 10, Pickerington North 7 
Nathan Barko’s 13-yard TD pass to Jordan Hay in the third quarter turned out to be the winning score, and Reynoldsburg (4-3, 2-2) held off visiting Pickerington North (3-4, 1-3) in the OCC Ohio. Cameron Young had 77 yards rushing for Reynoldsburg, which was outgained by 135 yards but had four interceptions. Bralen Wilson scored on a 8-yard run for Pickerington North.
